<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="92" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="11.[804,1399,1842,2261]" lastBlockId="11.[192,1398,2267,3482]" pageId="11" pageNumber="92">
Previously included in the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="F. Cuvier" authorityYear="1837" box="[1277,1399,1952,1985]" class="Mammalia" family="Dipodidae" genus="Allactaga" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="11" pageNumber="92" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Allactaga</taxonomicName>
and later Paralactaga, which has recently been found to be ajunior synonym of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gloger" authorityYear="1841" class="Mammalia" family="Dipodidae" genus="Scarturus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="11" pageNumber="92" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Scarturus</taxonomicName>
. Phylogenetically, S. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thomas" authorityYear="1920" box="[1176,1266,2078,2103]" class="Mammalia" family="Dipodidae" genus="Allactaga" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="11" pageNumber="92" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="hotsoni">hotsoni</taxonomicName>
occupies the basal position in the subgenus Paralactaga. Conspecific status of S. hotsoniand Allactagafirouzinamed by D. R. Womochel in 1978 was evident by morphometric analysis of G. I. Shenbrot in 2009 and was supported by molecular data of M. Dianat and colleagues in 2013. Two subspecies recognized.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
